<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-5119] Node.depthFirst() &apos;forgets&apos; text nodes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-5119</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Node.depthFirst() is expected to recursively include all Node.children() elements. The attached program demonstrates a counter example, where Node.depthFirst() &apos;forgets&apos; all 3 text chldren resulting in a list of 4 instead of 7 elements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct semantics of &quot;Node.depthFirst()&quot; is defined by &quot;depthFirst( node )&quot; in the attached program.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>(any)</environment>
